10:45.177 --> 10:46.679
What do you mean you
don't like Archie?

10:47.179 --> 10:48.180
It's a riot.

10:48.180 --> 10:51.183
You got your Jughead, your
Reggie, your Mr. Weatherbee.

10:53.185 --> 10:54.220
Please, stop crying, Maris.

10:54.687 --> 10:56.689
The doctor can always
cut off more next time.

11:04.196 --> 11:05.698
I'll be here when you wake up.

11:06.232 --> 11:07.233
Promise?

11:07.733 --> 11:08.734
Promise.

11:25.518 --> 11:27.019
MARTIN
: How come these places

11:27.019 --> 11:29.321
never have any
magazines for men?

11:29.588 --> 11:35.561
It's all hairdos
and recipes and butt exercises.

11:35.895 --> 11:38.964
I was just thinking
about what Niles said
about the hospital

11:38.964 --> 11:40.966
and the things
that happen here.

11:40.966 --> 11:42.735
Oh, geez, would you
look at this:

11:42.935 --> 11:45.805
"Ten Saucy Secrets
To Please Him In Bed."

11:45.805 --> 11:47.406
You know damn well
there are only four.

11:47.406 --> 11:50.976
The rest are just do-si-dos.

11:50.976 --> 11:53.779
It's like the whole
tapestry of life

11:53.779 --> 11:57.116
keeps replaying itself
within these walls.

11:57.116 --> 11:59.819
I used to bust people
for that one.

11:59.819 --> 12:01.120
You didn't hear a word
I said, did you?

12:01.620 --> 12:02.488
Yeah, I did.

12:02.488 --> 12:05.791
"Hospital...
tapestry of life."

12:06.292 --> 12:09.729
Whoa, that's a nice kitchen.

12:09.729 --> 12:12.631
.
You're a sentimental fool, Dad

12:14.133 --> 12:15.167
Well, here he is.

12:15.634 --> 12:18.671
Frasier, say hello
to your new brother.

12:19.171 --> 12:20.673
I don't like him.

12:26.011 --> 12:27.446
(chuckles)

12:27.446 --> 12:30.316
Remember when you were little
and you convinced Niles

12:30.316 --> 12:32.818
that we were all figments
of his imagination?

12:33.319 --> 12:34.754
The whole world was just
in his mind?

12:34.754 --> 12:38.190
I told him we disappeared
whenever he left the room.

12:38.190 --> 12:40.025
For months afterwards,

12:40.025 --> 12:41.861
he was always
darting into rooms

12:41.861 --> 12:44.363
to make sure we were
all still there.

12:44.363 --> 12:45.364
Scared the crap
out of me.

12:45.865 --> 12:46.866
I was ready
to kill you.

12:47.299 --> 12:48.367
What made you think of that?

12:48.801 --> 12:49.869
I don't know.

12:49.869 --> 12:52.371
Just thinking about Niles.

12:55.941 --> 12:57.510
Well, he must be all right.

12:57.510 --> 12:58.444
We're all still here.

13:02.381 --> 13:03.883
I don't think I've ever
been this frightened

13:03.883 --> 13:05.384
in my whole life.

13:05.384 --> 13:08.387
Well, Daph, according
to my timetable,

13:08.387 --> 13:11.690
Niles is probably
off the bypass pump by now.

13:11.957 --> 13:14.293
All the blockages
have been bypassed

13:14.493 --> 13:17.062
and the myocardium
is now receiving normal blood.

13:17.062 --> 13:18.564
How come you
know all this,

13:18.564 --> 13:20.933
but you're stumped by an electric
barbecue fork?

13:21.200 --> 13:24.670
Because the human heart was not
designed by some idiot in Japan.

13:25.037 --> 13:26.572
You know, Frasier,

13:26.972 --> 13:29.809
maybe now's not the perfect time to go into detail.

13:30.009 --> 13:31.043
It's all right, Roz.

13:31.477 --> 13:32.545
You see, she knows.

13:32.545 --> 13:35.481
Knowledge is our ally
against anxiety.

13:35.848 --> 13:37.883
Which happens to be the theme
for today's Best of Crane

13:37.883 --> 13:39.418
which is being broadcast
over the airwaves

13:39.418 --> 13:40.719
right this moment.

13:41.020 --> 13:43.589
Oh, yeah. They're piping it into the operating room

13:43.589 --> 13:44.890
instead of using anesthesia.

13:44.890 --> 13:48.060
Very funny, Roz.

13:48.060 --> 13:50.429
Oh, I hope the doctors
have their earplugs in,

13:50.429 --> 13:51.831
so they don't
fall asleep, too.

13:51.831 --> 13:53.232
All right, we get it.

13:53.232 --> 13:55.201
Seriously, if I was ever
going to rob a bank

13:55.201 --> 13:56.669
and I wanted to knock out
the guards...

13:56.669 --> 13:58.604
All right, Roz.

14:07.613 --> 14:10.015
Hey, is that
a Chunky in there?

14:12.418 --> 14:13.786
Looks like one.

14:13.786 --> 14:16.655
It's been a long time
since I seen one of those.

14:17.156 --> 14:18.591
What are they asking for it?

14:18.591 --> 14:23.662
Looks like it's 85 cents.

14:23.662 --> 14:26.098
Does it only take
the exact change?

14:26.098 --> 14:29.935
Looks like there's
a dollar slot.

14:29.935 --> 14:32.738
All I have is a ten.

14:32.738 --> 14:33.572
Will it take a ten?

14:33.572 --> 14:35.307
Get off your ass
and look.

14:36.575 --> 14:37.977
They usually just take singles.

14:37.977 --> 14:40.145
Anybody have a single?

14:42.948 --> 14:44.783
How can you think
about eating now?

14:44.783 --> 14:47.419
What would you rather
have me thinking about?

14:47.419 --> 14:48.254
I'll get you some change.

14:48.754 --> 14:49.755
Oh, thanks, Roz.

14:49.755 --> 14:54.193
I've been sitting
way too long, anyway.

14:54.627 --> 14:56.695
Excuse me... Colleen.

14:57.196 --> 14:59.498
Do you have any ones?

14:59.498 --> 15:00.733
I think so.
Let me check.

15:01.100 --> 15:03.168
Excuse me.
Can I help you?

15:03.669 --> 15:06.005
Yes. There's something
wrong with my baby.

15:06.272 --> 15:08.741
She has a little rash
on her cheek.

15:09.074 --> 15:10.142
I looked in the book

15:10.142 --> 15:12.077
and I don't think
it's chickenpox.

15:12.444 --> 15:14.446
But it does look
a little like scarlet fever.

15:14.780 --> 15:16.348
Is this your first child?

15:16.348 --> 15:17.283
Yes. Why?

15:17.650 --> 15:19.218
I think
this is lipstick.

15:19.218 --> 15:20.219
Would a five help?

15:20.719 --> 15:22.087
No, I'm afraid I need ones.

15:22.087 --> 15:23.455
Oh, thank God.

15:23.455 --> 15:25.457
Oh, look at that.

15:25.457 --> 15:28.260
That's probably
how it happened.

15:28.494 --> 15:33.032
Thank you.
Colleen, I won't forget you.

15:33.499 --> 15:35.367
I'm sorry.
All I've got are fives.

15:35.567 --> 15:36.635
Oh, thanks, anyway.

15:36.635 --> 15:37.536
Do I know you?

15:37.903 --> 15:39.471
I don't think so.

15:39.905 --> 15:41.807
Are you sure?

15:42.107 --> 15:44.009
Trust me, I'm really good with faces. Thanks.

15:45.911 --> 15:46.879
Mrs. Crane?
Yes?

15:46.879 --> 15:48.380
Your husband's
doing well.

15:48.380 --> 15:50.883
He's off the pump
and his heart is
beating on its own.

15:50.883 --> 15:52.384
FRASIER:
How's his blood pressure?

15:52.384 --> 15:53.218
100/60.

15:53.218 --> 15:54.586
Could be better.

15:54.586 --> 15:57.089
Did you thoroughly suction
the cardioplegic solution?

15:57.589 --> 15:58.490
You see, I'm a doctor.

15:58.490 --> 16:00.392
Oh, yes, Dr. Schafer told me
about you.

16:00.893 --> 16:02.895
He said if you started
asking me questions,

16:02.895 --> 16:04.196
I should do this.

16:06.999 --> 16:11.003
Oh, I get it.
Very nice.

16:11.003 --> 16:13.505
Well, that's
good news, right?

16:13.505 --> 16:14.506
Oh, yeah, great.

16:14.506 --> 16:15.307
They didn't have
any change.

16:15.541 --> 16:17.109
Oh, shoot.

16:27.686 --> 16:29.822
What you reading, Daph?

16:29.822 --> 16:32.591
I have no idea.

16:32.591 --> 16:35.594
I must have read
the same paragraph ten times.

16:35.594 --> 16:37.463
I don't know how
you're getting through this.

16:37.463 --> 16:39.365
Well, it's not like the old days

16:39.365 --> 16:41.867
when heart surgery
was a big thing.

16:41.867 --> 16:43.369
Nowadays, they
do it so much,

16:43.369 --> 16:45.371
it's like going in for a haircut.

16:45.871 --> 16:48.173
You read the paper and
wait till he's done.

16:48.173 --> 16:50.275
But aren't you scared?

16:53.979 --> 16:56.849
Uh, I wonder if that
guy has a dollar.

16:56.849 --> 17:03.288
I bet he does.
Excuse me.

17:03.288 --> 17:06.290
Oh, no!

17:06.290 --> 17:07.291
What, Daph?

17:07.291 --> 17:09.261
I don't believe this.
Excuse me.

17:09.261 --> 17:10.262
What?

17:10.262 --> 17:12.263
I was supposed to bring
Niles's cell phone

17:12.765 --> 17:14.299
in case any of his
patients called

17:14.299 --> 17:16.068
so I could refer them
to Dr. Wells.

17:16.068 --> 17:18.303
Now, I'm going to be calling
his stupid cell phone

17:18.303 --> 17:20.172
every two minutes
to check his mailbox.

17:20.172 --> 17:22.007
Here, let's use
my cell phone, all right?

17:22.007 --> 17:23.409
We can take turns calling.

17:23.409 --> 17:25.778
He asked me to do
this one simple thing

17:26.278 --> 17:28.280
and I forgot.
I'm such an idiot.

17:28.280 --> 17:30.282
Don't go beating yourself up.

17:30.282 --> 17:32.284
You didn't do
anything wrong.

17:32.284 --> 17:35.287
Come on.
I'll dial first.

17:35.287 --> 17:37.289
Now, look, Niles,
as far as Dad knows

17:37.289 --> 17:39.792
I had nothing to do
with your leg breaking, right?

17:40.292 --> 17:41.160
You pushed me.

17:41.160 --> 17:43.028
Yes, and in exchange
for your silence,

17:43.028 --> 17:44.029
you'll get ten
of my records.

17:44.029 --> 17:45.030
Any ones you want.

17:45.030 --> 17:47.032
Even the Shostakovich?

17:47.032 --> 17:48.033
Not that one.

17:48.534 --> 17:49.501
Then forget it.

17:49.501 --> 17:51.970
Okay, fine.

17:51.970 --> 17:54.039
Sign here
and initial here.

17:55.808 --> 17:59.278
You still in bed, Mr. Lazybones?

17:59.611 --> 18:01.180
If you're going to lie around all day

18:01.180 --> 18:02.681
I got you something to read.

18:02.681 --> 18:04.183
The Charterhouse of Parma?

18:04.683 --> 18:06.185
Better. Archie.

18:07.152 --> 18:09.621
Well, hello, Chunky.

18:09.621 --> 18:10.589
I beg your pardon?

18:10.956 --> 18:12.491
Got some change.

18:12.491 --> 18:14.026
Congratulations.

18:22.568 --> 18:24.570
Hey, is that
a Marathon bar?

18:25.003 --> 18:26.972
Oh, geez, now I don't know
what to get.

18:27.272 --> 18:28.340
You should go with your
first instinct, Dad.

18:28.841 --> 18:29.842
I haven't had
a Marathon bar in years.

18:29.842 --> 18:31.210
All right, then
get a Marathon bar.

18:31.510 --> 18:32.578
Come to think of it,

18:32.578 --> 18:35.047
I think they quit making
Marathons back in the '80s.

18:35.481 --> 18:38.550
Then you should get a Chunky.

18:38.550 --> 18:40.052
Uh, although...

18:40.052 --> 18:41.553
I kind of want
to get a Marathon bar

18:41.553 --> 18:42.821
just to see what
it looks like
on the inside.

18:43.021 --> 18:44.089
All right,
just get the Chunky!

18:44.089 --> 18:46.892
All right.

18:46.892 --> 18:48.160
Hey!
What?

18:48.627 --> 18:50.129
It's stuck!

18:50.129 --> 18:51.663
Oh, great,
you had to have Chunky!

18:52.164 --> 18:53.665
Oh, fine! All right!
I'll get it!

18:55.167 --> 18:57.002
What is going on?

18:57.002 --> 18:58.237
We have a stuck Chunky.

18:58.237 --> 19:01.240
Why did Chunky
stick his arm in there?

19:01.240 --> 19:05.210
Not me, the candy.

19:05.711 --> 19:07.713
Oh, I give up.

19:07.713 --> 19:08.714
Don't worry, Martin.

19:08.714 --> 19:10.716
I'll stop by tomorrow
and get us some Godiva.

19:11.216 --> 19:13.719
But I want my Chunky.

19:13.719 --> 19:15.220
Excuse me.

19:21.960 --> 19:23.395
Chunky, was it?

19:29.401 --> 19:30.402
Oh, oh, Daphne.

19:30.936 --> 19:32.437
It's okay.
It's okay.

19:32.437 --> 19:34.773
Everything's going
to be fine.

19:34.773 --> 19:36.441
Do I need to call security here?

19:36.441 --> 19:37.809
Uh, no, it's all right.

19:37.809 --> 19:38.744
I'm sorry about this.

19:38.744 --> 19:40.078
Kind of a tough time.

19:40.078 --> 19:41.413
All right, but keep
this area clear

19:41.413 --> 19:42.915
until I can get it cleaned up.

19:42.915 --> 19:45.384
Right. And we'll pay for this.

19:45.384 --> 19:47.653
I already paid for this.

19:50.923 --> 19:52.925
Daphne, I know
you're in hell right now,

19:52.925 --> 19:54.927
but in just about
20 minutes,

19:54.927 --> 19:58.430
comes the disconnecting
of the ventilator
and the extubation.

19:58.931 --> 20:00.933
You can see it all
in the diagram
on page 24-C.

20:00.933 --> 20:01.900
He's not a diagram!

20:01.900 --> 20:03.402
He's my husband

20:03.402 --> 20:05.404
and he's on a table
with his chest cut open!

20:05.404 --> 20:08.907
I'm sorry if I can't handle
this as well as the rest of you,

20:08.907 --> 20:10.409
but I'm terrified!

20:10.409 --> 20:12.711
Daphne, it's okay.
Just calm down.

20:12.711 --> 20:14.479
When all this is over...

20:14.479 --> 20:16.448
There is no
"when this is over"!

20:16.448 --> 20:19.351
There's no tomorrow,
no next week, no next year!

20:19.351 --> 20:21.853
There's nothing until
he comes out of there

20:21.853 --> 20:23.121
and I know he's okay!

20:24.456 --> 20:25.924
Daphne...

20:25.924 --> 20:27.759
Why don't you sit down, son?

20:33.665 --> 20:36.134
Nobody meant anything.

20:36.134 --> 20:39.137
It's hard as hell for
all of us to be here.

20:39.638 --> 20:42.641
I know. It's just...

20:43.141 --> 20:44.142
I hate hospitals.

20:44.643 --> 20:45.444
I hate them.

20:45.444 --> 20:47.613
I hate all of this.

20:47.613 --> 20:48.947
I know.

20:54.953 --> 20:58.957
.
I'm afraid your wife's X rays don't look good

21:11.003 --> 21:13.505
Waiting is the hardest part.

21:20.512 --> 21:23.015
Niles...

21:23.015 --> 21:24.516
you did great.

21:25.017 --> 21:28.020
The doctor said
it went even better
than he expected.

21:28.020 --> 21:30.522
I'm so proud of you.

21:31.023 --> 21:32.024
He'll be out all night.

21:32.524 --> 21:35.027
Why don't you get
something to eat?

21:35.027 --> 21:38.030
I'll be here
when you wake up.

22:18.537 --> 22:21.540
Say hello to your new sister.

22:23.542 --> 22:25.544
Look, she's smiling at you.

22:34.553 --> 22:36.555
♪♪ Hey, baby,
I hear the blues a-calling ♪
